Running below which is rewritten from UVM tests/20sequences/10sequence_lib/3567_default_type gives a Verilator assertion:

```
%Error: Internal Error: t/t_0.v:21:41: ../V3Broken.cpp:182: Broken link in node (or something without maybePointedTo): 'm_varp && !m_varp->brokeExists()' @ ./V3Ast__gen_impl.h:6079
   21 |       foreach (m_typewide_sequences[i]) sequences.push_back(m_typewide_sequences[i]);
      |                                         ^~~~~~~~~
```

```
module t;

  class uvm_sequence_library #(
      type REQ = int,
      RSP = int
  );
    int sequences[$];
  endclass

  class Cls1 extends uvm_sequence_library;

    static int m_typewide_sequences[$];

    function void init_sequence_library();
      foreach (m_typewide_sequences[i]) sequences.push_back(m_typewide_sequences[i]);
    endfunction
  endclass

  initial $finish;

endmodule
```

I'll get back to this eventually, but anyone else that wants to investigate is very welcome to, thanks.

